1) Environment → metaphor → meaning

You already refined it well:

Environments don’t determine beliefs; they bias the metaphors and problems people organize around.

	•	Desert → scarcity, obedience, endurance
	•	River valley → cycles, renewal, fertility
	•	Sea → uncertainty, navigation, exchange

Think of environment as a constraint field that nudges which stories are stable and useful.

