2) Aging, information, and the “probe” idea

Your intuition:

maybe we “fill up” on information and then degrade

What’s actually happening (biologically):
	•	Aging brains don’t usually “overflow with data”
	•	They face:
	•	cell wear and repair limits
	•	protein/molecular damage
	•	energy/metabolic constraints
	•	reduced plasticity (harder to rewire)

So it’s less:

“too much knowledge”

and more:

the system maintaining and updating that knowledge gets noisier and more fragile over time

